@coffeekraken.s-date-picker-component.js.name: Date Picker
@coffeekraken.s-date-picker-component.js.description:
This component specify a date picker. It uses under the hood the **AMAZING pikaday library** with some additional features like
sugar theming support as well as some events and more.
Almost all the pikaday options are available through properties. Check out the api documentation for more details...

example.title: Min and max dates
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
     <s-date-picker
         placeholder="Choose a date"
         class="s-width:40"
         min-date="2021-08-10"
         max-date="2021-08-20"
         name="myDatePicker2"
         input
     ></s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: Disable weekends
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        class="s-width:40"
        name="myDatePicker3"
        disable-weekends
        input
    ></s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: With a button
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        class="s-width:40"
        name="myDatePicker4"
        input
        button
    ></s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: Disabled
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        class="s-width:40"
        name="myDatePicker4"
         disabled
        input
        button
    ></s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: Display more than 1 month
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        class="s-width:40"
        name="myDatePicker4"
        number-of-months="2"
         input
         button
    ></s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: With custom input
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
     <s-date-picker name="something">
         <input type="text" name="something" placeholder="Choose a date" class="s-width:40" />
     </s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: With a custom button
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        name="myDatePicker5"
    >
      <button class="s-btn">Choose a date</button>
    </s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: With a custom input and button
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive">
     Choose a date
    <s-date-picker
        placeholder="Choose a date"
        name="myDatePicker5"
    >
      <input type="text" name="something" placeholder="Choose a date" class="s-width:40" />
      <button class="s-btn">Choose a date</button>
    </s-date-picker>
</label>

example.title: RTL Support
example.code:
<label class="s-label:responsive" dir="rtl">
     Choose a date

        name="myDatePicker1"
        input

</label>
